Turkey Preparing New Small Business Support, Hurriyet Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-02-25T05:54:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-25/turkey-preparing-new-small-business-support-hurriyet-reports.html
  Turkey ’s government is preparing a
support package for small businesses worth up to four billion
liras ($2.5 billion), Hurriyet newspaper said, citing Industry
Minister Nihat Ergun.  The package will help companies win low-cost financing,
Ergun said, according to the Istanbul-based newspaper. The aim
is to help 100,000 small companies, particularly those that
didn’t benefit from similar offers in 2009 and 2010, Ergun said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
